{
  "text": "Formal concept analysis (FCA) [CITATION_1] studies the way conceptual structures emerge out of observations. Basic FCA considers an incidence relation over a pair of sets (objects, further denoted by numbers) and (attributes, denoted by lower-case letters). Binary relations are introduced as formal contexts ! \" ! $ #",
